hopobject.body: Can you hear me OK? atomoxetine medscape This is a sore point of sorts, in that the abstract's release dovetails with the Institutes of Medicine's recent findings that cancer care is falling short, just as the cancer population is poised to spike. Among the IOM's findings were that doctors are not sufficiently discussing care options, including palliative care, with patients and that a majority of patients mistakenly believe the care they are receiving will cure them of their disease.
